      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWAN BAY MISS (7) settled well back early on debut and boxed on fairly to finish fourth (18.06) at this track over 300m. Looks suited here and big improvement expected. OUR BILL (1) has mixed form recently, finishing seventh (18.48) in a Maiden at this track latest but did run well two back when in the frame. Good beginner and aided by the inside draw. Can turn it around this time. MULWEE HARRY (2) did a good job to finish second last time out over 272m at The Gardens (16.18) in a Maiden, the second top-three finish on the trot. Good beginner aided by a handy draw. Expecting sharp improvement this line-up. TUNCURRY BLUE (8) collected a minor prize last start and must be considered.",
